list.title: Aire Ancient Baths
list.description: Spa with a variety of pools and saunas to relax in before your treatment.

list.title: Akiko Nails
list.description: Nail salon that specializing in Japanese nail art technique. They have many suggested designs or can create something specifically for you.

list.title: Ballet Beautiful
list.description: Mary Helen Bowers was a professional ballerina who created a workout that sculpts and tones your body, inspired by ballet movements.

list.title: Bamford Haybarn Spa
list.description: Bamford Haybarn Spa's first location was in the English countryside, and the tranquility has been transported to the location in New York. The ingredients in the skincare are natural and organic.

list.title: Breathe Salt Room
list.description: Salt rooms are made from Himalayan salt, which supports healthy breathing. Take their yoga class in here.

list.title: BrickHouse Ceramics
list.description: Ceramics studio located in Long Island City. There are pottery classes for various skill levels and techniques.

list.title: Brooklyn Bridge Park
list.description: Park with waterfront views of Manhattan and restaurants in the nearby area.

list.title: Chelsea Piers (Pier 62)
list.description: Pier with a large park on the river. At Chelsea Piers you can go rock climbing or use their driving range.

list.title: Chillhouse
list.description: Spa and café that offers massages and manicures in a contemporary and bright environment.

list.title: Clayworks On Columbia
list.description: Pottery school offering classes as well as studio space in a friendly environment.

list.title: Erika Bloom Pilates
list.description: Private pilates sessions and holistic healing including acupuncture and rolfing. There are multiple locations outside of New York City to check out too.

list.title: European Wax Center
list.description: Fast and convenient waxing chain that offers customer loyalty programs.

list.title: Great Jones Spa
list.description: Spa with a water lounge, steam room, and sauna while you wait for your treatment.

list.title: Greenpoint- Williamsburg Waterfront
list.description: Newly developed waterfront park with views of the Manhattan skyline.

list.title: Hortus Nailworks
list.description: Nail and sugaring studio located in the Lower East Side. The products they use are all natural and organic.

list.title: Inscape
list.description: Modern meditation studio with an app to continue your practice at home.

list.title: Metrograph
list.description: Metrograph shows independent premiers and repertory programs. The theater is beautiful and they have one of the best candy selections we've seen at a cinema.

list.title: New York Pilates
list.description: Pilates studio offering reformer classes and private lesson with skilled instructors who can help you to reach your goals.

list.title: Paintbox
list.description: Manicure studio in SoHo with an impressive selection of nail art that changes seasonally in a beautiful space.

list.title: Riverside Park
list.description: Park stretching four miles along the Hudson River.

list.title: Skin Laundry
list.description: Skin Laundry specializes in laser facials that are more accessibly priced and designed to be scheduled regularly.

list.title: St. Luke in the Fields Garden
list.description: Attached to the beautiful and inclusive Church of St. Luke in the Fields, the garden is open from 10am to dusk daily.

list.title: Sundays Nail Studio
list.description: Sundays specializes in nontoxic nail polish in a minimalist space.

list.title: Tenoverten
list.description: Nontoxic nail salon in a beautiful space with comfortable chairs.

list.title: Textile Arts Center
list.description: Studio offering textile related classes including fabric dyeing techniques, basket making, sewing, and knitting.

list.title: The Class By Taryn Toomey
list.description: The Class is both a physical and emotional workout. Taryn Toomey developed this revolutionary program based in yoga and cardio that works to restore a mind-body connection.

list.title: The Ramble
list.description: Area of Central Park that is full of winding pathways, benches, and overhanging trees. One of the few places in Manhattan you might not see people around you.

list.title: Valley Nails
list.description: Serene nail studio with innovative designs.

list.title: Woom Center
list.description: Meditation and yoga studio utilizing sound vibration to center you. The combination of futuristic and ancient techniques make this studio unique.

list.title: Yoga Vida
list.description: Yoga Vida's classes are suitable for all levels, as the instructor will offer moderations on many of the poses.
